Detailed Description

cvmx_pcs::_int::_reg

PCS Interrupt Register NOTE: RXERR and TXERR conditions to be discussed with Dan before finalising DBG_SYNC interrupt fires when code group synchronization state machine makes a transition from SYNC_ACQUIRED_1 state to SYNC_ACQUIRED_2 state(See IEEE 802.3-2005 figure 37-9). It is an indication that a bad code group was received after code group synchronizaton was achieved. This interrupt should be disabled during normal link operation. Use it as a debug help feature only.
